author: from staff reports
title: Simpson's late goal lifts Allegany over Cecil, 2-1
text:
Simpson's late goal lifts Allegany over Cecil, 2-1 from staff reports   
ARNOLD — Matthew Simpson scored the deciding goal with 46 seconds left in regulation to give Allegany College of Maryland a 2-1 road win over Cecil Tuesday in Maryland JUCO Soccer. 
The Seahawks struck first when Dylan Brilloud scored unassisted with 30 minutes remaining in the first half. Jerry Washington had the first Trojans goal to tie the score before 50 minutes of silence followed until Simpson broke the tie. 
Simpson’s goal was a header off of a free kick by John Anderson. 
“We only traveled with 11 boys, so for them to fight like they did for 90 minutes and be able to come away with a win is something I’m very proud of,” said ACM coach Rick Zimmerman. 
Allegany College (4-8) will play today, at home, against Potomac State at 4 p.m. 
York 1, Frostburg State 0 
YORK, Pa. — Greg Bechard scored the only goal of the game and York handed Frostburg State its second conference loss Tuesday in Capital Athletic Conference men’s soccer. 
Bechard’s goal, which came on an assist from Ryan Ockford, came in the 64th minute. 
York (6-6-2, 3-1-1) led in shots 16-12 and in corner kicks 4-3. 
Hassan Mostafa made three saves in goal for Frostburg (8-4-1, 2-2-1). The Bobcats host St. Mary’s in their Homecoming game Saturday at 5 p.m.
